Package EasyOverrider

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ParamDescription<O,P>
    This represents a parameter in an object and how to get and set it.
    ParamListService
    This interface describes a class that will house the interesting functionality used to generate toString, hashCode, and equals results using ParamList objects.
    RecursionPreventingToString
    Interface to implement when you have a possibly recursive toString() method.
    This interface defines two methods: toString(Map) - must be implemented primaryToString() - only needs to be implemented if your ParamList contains primary parameters.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EasyOverriderUtils
    A static class containing various generic methods used by EasyOverrider.
    ParamDescriptionBase<O,P>
    An abstract class that implements most of the functionality of a ParamDescription.
    ParamDescriptionCollection<O,E,P extends Collection<? extends E>>
    Describes a standard Collection parameter in an object.
    ParamDescriptionMap<O,K,V,P extends Map<? extends K,? extends V>>
    Describes a standard Map parameter in an object.
    ParamDescriptionSingle<O,P>
    Describes a standard parameter in an object.
    ParamList<O>
    Describes a list of parameters that describe the parameters in a class.
    These objects can then be used to easily override the toString, hashCode, and equals methods with standard behaviors.
    ParamListBuilder<O>
    Class to help with building the building of a ParamList.
    Since the ParamList and ParamDescription objects are pretty complicated, this class helps create them in a nice, fluent way.
    ParamListServiceConfig
    This houses any configuration pieces that should be available to the ParamListService.
    ParamListServiceImpl
    The default implementation of a ParamListService.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ParamMethodRestriction
    Enum to make it easier to dictate which methods a parameter should be included in.
    ParamMethodRestrictionRestriction
    This enum dictates which ParamMethodRestriction values are available for use.
    It is here so that using the unsafe ones requires effort and thought before being used.
    The default value is ParamMethodRestrictionRestriction.SAFE_ONLY, but if, for some reason, you decided that you want the __UNSAFE values, you can use ParamMethodRestrictionRestriction.ALLOW_UNSAFE.
